  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Always use scope:</strong> The <code>scope</code> attribute is essential for screen readers to associate headers with data cells</li>
      <li><strong>Screen reader announcement:</strong> When navigating to a data cell, the associated headers are announced</li>
      <li><strong>Complex tables:</strong> For tables with multiple header levels, consider using the <code>headers</code> attribute on <a href="/docs/elements/native/td/"><code>&lt;td&gt;</code></a> elements</li>
      <li><strong>Implicit roles:</strong> <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> has an implicit ARIA role of <code>columnheader</code> (with <code>scope="col"</code>) or <code>rowheader</code> (with <code>scope="row"</code>)</li>
      <li><strong>Sort state:</strong> When a column is sorted, use <code>aria-sort="ascending"</code> or <code>aria-sort="descending"</code> on the <code>&lt;th&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

